## Architecture Summary Diagram

```
main.py
 ├── CLI  → run_pipeline_cli → run_pipeline
 │                           ├── PM Mode (claude-agent-sdk Task tool)
 │                           └── Orchestrated Mode (Python loops)
 │                               ├── AgentEngine Protocol
 │                               │   ├── ClaudeEngine (claude-agent-sdk query())
 │                               │   ├── CopilotEngine (github-copilot-sdk sessions)
 │                               │   ├── CodexEngine (codex-app-server-sdk threads)
 │                               │   ├── OpenAIEngine (openai chat completions + tool loop)
 │                               │   └── MockEngine (canned responses, no API)
 │                               └── Checkpoint → save/load → run_state table
 └── Server → FastAPI (uvicorn)
             ├── RunManager (queue, execute, track, resume)
             ├── OLamoDb (SQLite: runs/events/run_state/agent_sessions)
             ├── SseBroadcaster (fan-out to web clients)
             └── SettingsStore (olamo-settings.json, lock/unlock)
```

**Key patterns:**
- **Protocol-based engines**: `AgentEngine` Protocol allows plugging in any LLM backend
- **Event-driven**: Every agent action emits events → broadcast via SSE + persisted to DB
- **Resumable at 4 layers**: pipeline checkpoints, DB state, run status recovery, agent sessions
- **Concurrency control**: `asyncio.Semaphore(max_concurrent=5)` limits parallel runs
- **Settings lock**: Global settings locked during run execution; updates deferred until unlock
