## 5. Main Pipeline Flow

### Entry Point: `/Users/anil/Source/OLamo/main.py`

```
main()
├── --server mode → uvicorn.run(create_app())        # Web server (FastAPI)
└── CLI mode   → run_pipeline_cli(task, ...)
                 └── run_pipeline(task, settings, on_event, ...)
                     ├── "pm" mode       → run_pipeline_pm()
                     └── "orchestrated"  → run_pipeline_orchestrated()
```

### Orchestrated Mode Full Flow (`run_pipeline_orchestrated`):

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  INIT: Resolve engines (Claude/Copilot/Codex/OpenAI) │
│         Headless? → MockEngine for all roles        │
└──────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────┘
                       ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  STAGE 1: Design Loop                               │
│  1. lead-developer creates plan from task           │
│  2. FOR max_design_cycles:                          │
│     a. qa-engineer REVIEW DESIGN                    │
│     b. If APPROVED → break                          │
│     c. lead-developer REFINE based on QA findings   │
│  3. [Optional] Human Approval Gate                  │
│     → Feedback loop: refine → re-QA → re-review     │
│  4. SAVE CHECKPOINT (stage=1)                       │
└──────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────┘
                       ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  STAGE 2: Implementation Loop                       │
│  FOR max_impl_cycles:                               │
│    1. developer implements from plan                │
│    2. Build Loop (max_build_cycles):                │
│       a. build-agent builds/tests                   │
│       b. If SUCCESS → ok                            │
│       c. Else developer FIX BUILD FAILURE            │
│    3. Parallel Review (code-reviewer + qa-engineer  │
│       + lead-developer) via asyncio.gather          │
│    4. If CRITICAL findings → re-invite approved     │
│    5. If no NEEDS_IMPROVEMENT → break               │
│    6. SAVE CHECKPOINT (stage=1)                     │
│  7. repo-manager: Commit & Create PR                │
│  8. SAVE CHECKPOINT (stage=3)                       │
└──────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────┘
                       ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  STAGE 3b: CI Check Polling (max_pr_cycles)         │
│  1. repo-manager POLL CI CHECKS                     │
│  2. If FAILING → developer fixes → rebuild → push  │
└──────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────┘
                       ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  STAGE 4: PR Poll Loop (max_pr_cycles)              │
│  1. repo-manager POLL PR COMMENTS                  │
│  2. If NO ACTIONABLE → done                         │
│  3. Extract comment IDs → MARK ADDRESSED            │
│  4. developer addresses comments                    │
│  5. build-agent verifies                            │
│  6. Reviewer pass (all 3 reviewers in parallel)     │
│  7. If findings → developer fixes → rebuild → push │
│  8. SAVE CHECKPOINT (stage=3)                       │
└──────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────┘
                       ▼
              "Pipeline complete. PR: ..."
```

### Web Server Flow (`create_app` in `/Users/anil/Source/OLamo/app/web/app.py`):

```
FastAPI lifespan:
  setup() → Open DB, recover stale runs, spawn queued runs
  ↑ serve requests
  close() → Cancel tasks, close DB

API Endpoints:
  GET  /                          → SPA index.html
  GET  /api/events                → SSE stream (with gap-fill via Last-Event-ID)
  GET/POST /api/runs              → List/Create runs
  POST /api/runs/{id}/resume      → Resume interrupted run
  GET/POST /api/runs/{id}/approval → Design approval gate
  GET  /api/runs/{id}/events      → Event history
  GET  /api/runs/{id}/state       → Live run state
  GET  /api/team                  → Agent configs & pipeline stages
  GET/PUT /api/settings           → Settings CRUD
  GET  /api/prs                   → GitHub PR list
  GET  /api/prs/auth              → GH auth status
```

**RunManager execution** (`_execute_run`, line 149):
1. Set status RUNNING, create log dir
2. Lock settings store
3. Merge per-run settings override
4. Load checkpoint from DB
5. Wire up `on_event` (broadcast + DB persist + run_state update)
6. Wire up `on_approval_required` (ApprovalGate + spec persistence)
7. Call `run_pipeline(...)` with checkpoint + save_checkpoint callback
8. On success → COMPLETED, on error → FAILED
9. Unlock settings store

